<a href="https://thekamboshop.com/">Angico</a>, specifically the Angico tree (Anadenanthera colubrina), is a revered plant in South American indigenous cultures, known for its medicinal and spiritual uses. The tree's bark, seeds, and resin are utilized in various traditional practices. One of the most notable uses of Angico is in the preparation of Yopo, a potent psychoactive snuff made from its seeds. 
